1 Introduction ü§Ø
****************

Dslide is conducts presentations in Emacs and can utilize anything and
everything that Emacs can do.  Abstractly, a presentation is a scripted
sequence of content.  Org mode documents are the primary means of
encoding these sequences for dslide.

   What dslide primarily adds to Emacs and Org Mode:

   ‚Ä¢ Simplified user interface suitable for a presentation remote
     controller
   ‚Ä¢ Data model that adapts Emacs to this interface, including Org babel
     and keyboard macros
   ‚Ä¢ Method of attaching reusable, configurable programmed behavior to
     org mode content
   ‚Ä¢ Extensible framework for creating custom programmed behavior
   ‚Ä¢ Presenter tools such as viewing hidden content invisible to the
     audience

* Menu:

* Design Goals ü•Ö::              Things Hopefully Achieved
* Strengths ü¶æ::                 When Dslide is Perfect


