8.1.1 Life Cycles
-----------------

Owning an object also means out-living it.  This is important to
understanding the sequence of events.  The methods used for the
lifecycle are part of dslide‚Äôs *note Stateful Sequence: Stateful
Sequence.  Every lifecyle starts with ‚Äòdslide-begin‚Äô or ‚Äòdslide-end‚Äô
(depending on whether we go forward or backward) and ends with
‚Äòdslide-final‚Äô.

   The state of the slide out-lives the state of its slide action.  The
slide action out-lives both child slides and section actions.  Child
slides and section actions life cycles may overlap.

   The child and section actions orders can vary depending on the slide
action‚Äôs choices.  There may be multiple children alive at one time.
The children may complete after, before, or at the same time as the
section actions.

   *Going forward:*

  1. slide ‚Äòdslide-begin‚Äô
  2. slide action ‚Äòdslide-begin‚Äô
  3. section actions + child slides ‚Äòdslide-begin‚Äô
  4. section actions + child slides ‚Äòdslide-final‚Äô
  5. slide action ‚Äòdslide-final‚Äô
  6. slide ‚Äòdslide-final‚Äô

   *Going backward:*

  1. slide ‚Äòdslide-end‚Äô
  2. slide action ‚Äòdslide-end‚Äô
  3. child slides + section actions ‚Äòdslide-end‚Äô
  4. child slides + section actions ‚Äòdslide-final‚Äô
  5. slide action ‚Äòdslide-final‚Äô
  6. slide ‚Äòdslide-final‚Äô


